import React, {useState} from 'react';
import { Typography } from '@material-ui/core';
import { Button } from '@material-ui/core';
import {Grid} from '@material-ui/core';
import ExpandMoreIcon from '@material-ui/icons/ExpandMore';
import Skill from './Skill';

const Skills = () => {
    return (
        <Grid container
        direction="row"
        justify="flex-start"
        alignItems="center"
        style={{marginLeft:'30px'}}>

            <Grid item xs={12}>
                <Typography
                display="block"
                justifyContent="center"
                align="center"
                variant="h4"
                style={{opacity:'100%', fontWeight:'bold', fontSize:'40px', marginBottom:'0', color:'white'}}>
                    Skills
                </Typography>
            </Grid>

            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 1'
            className='skill'/>
            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 2'/>
            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 3'/>
            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 4'/>
            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 5'/>
            <Skill 
            skillName='skill 6'/>

        </Grid>
    )
}

export default Skills;
